<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Session to Open June 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The chairpersons of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress may no longer write
congratulatory inscriptions or attend ceremonial activities
including ribbon cutting, award giving, movie premieres or
ceremonies celebrating the debuts of books, unless the activities
are organized by the Party Central Committee or the NPC Standing
Committee itself.
</P>
<P>
The draft regulation, aimed at enabling top legislators to
concentrate on addressing priority issues of state, was approved
in principle here today by the fourth chairpersons' meeting of the
NPC Standing Committee, presided over by Li Peng, the standing
committee's chairman.
</P>
<P>
The meeting decided that the NPC Standing Committee would hold
its third meeting here June 22 through June 26.
</P>
<P>
It suggested that the upcoming meeting should deliberate the
draft law on special economic regions and the continental shelf,
the draft law on licensed doctors, the revised draft law on land
management and a State Council motion for revising the law on
organizing village committees.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to examine and approve the report on
the central treasury's 1997 final account by the Ministry of
Finance, in addition to examining and approving several other
State Council motions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Standing Committee of the Ninth Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference is to convene its second meeting
June 16 to 19, it was also announced here today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
