<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Meets Young Scientists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met with
young scientists from both China and overseas here today.
</P>
<P>
The scientists are some of the 150 delegates attending an
ongoing conference on manufacturing science.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Li gave them an introduction to the
strategy taken by the Chinese government to revitalize the country
by means of science and education, encouraging them to actively
participate in Sino-foreign scientific co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Li also gave an account of the country's current economic
situation, the steps taken by the Chinese government to cope with
the Asian financial crisis and the Chinese government's stand on
maintaining the stability of the RMB yuan (the Chinese currency).
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
