<HEADLINE> Russian Experts Leave to Examine U.S. Strategic Sites </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 15 (Xinhua) -- A team of Russian experts left
Monday for the United States to examine the strategic military
sites in line with the Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty (START-1).
</P>
<P>
Under the START-1 treaty which came into effect in December
1994, the total number of deployed intercontinental ballistic
missiles (ICBMs) aboard submarines and heavy bombers should be
reduced to no more than 1,600 units carrying a total of no more
than 6,000 warheads.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the treaty, various methods can be used to
monitor the observance of obligations, including technical means
of verification, 12 kinds of on-the-spot inspections, a regular
exchange of information on strategic offensive weapons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
