<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cardiff EU Summit Issues Declaration on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARDIFF, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) leaders
attending the Cardiff EU summit Monday afternoon issued a special
declaration on Kosovo, condemning the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia's (FRY) use of force against ethnic Albanians in
Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The European leaders said in the statement that the worsening
crisis in Kosovo "constitutes a serious threat to regional
stability and requires a strong and united international
response."
</P>
<P>
The EU leaders urged the Yugoslav government to stop all
operations by the security forces in Kosovo, enable "effective and
continuous international monitoring in Kosovo", facilitate the
full return of refugees to their homes and make rapid progress in
the political dialogue with Kosovo Albanian leadership.
</P>
<P>
On the meeting between Russian President Boris Yeltsin and
Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic in Moscow on Tuesday, the
leaders urged President Milosevic to take advantage of the
opportunity to announce progress on the above measures.
</P>
<P>
"Unless these four steps are taken without delay, a much
stronger response, of a qualitatively different order, will be
required from the international community to deal with the
increased threat to regional peace and stability," the statement
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
