<HEADLINE> England Coach Delight at Team's Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MASERILLE, June 15 (Xinhua) -- England head coach Glenn Hoddle was
delighted to see his team's performance in the match against Tunisia
which they won 2-0 here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Captain Alan Shearer scored in the first half while Paul Scholes
added one in the second half to give England their victory.
</P>
<P>
"That was a great start for us," said Hoddle, "It was a bit
anxious having to wait for our first match, but I felt we could have
had three or four and really taken them to the cleaners. But
overall it was a fantastic performance."
</P>
<P>
"I'm a great admirer of Paul, that is why I brought him into the
team so quickly once I'd taken over." Hoddle said.
</P>
<P>
Hoddle said:"A lot of good things came from England today and
Scholes was behind them."
</P>
<P>
Hoddle praised the England supporters inside the stadium:"The
support we got out here today was magnificent. There was no trouble
in the ground."
</P>
<P>
But during the match, clash broke out between England and
Tunisian fans on the beach of Mariselle. 
</P>
