<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "Cobra" Ilie Makes Deadly Bite for Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LYON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- "Cobra" Adrian Ilie made a deadly bite
here on Monday when his first half goal gave Romania a 1-0 win over
Colombia in Group G of the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Romania, quarterfinalists at the last World Cup in the United
States, clinched the victory through the Valencia striker in the
injury time of the first half.
</P>
<P>
Romania, who defeated the same opponent 3-1 in the United States
four years ago, gave the Colombians scare repeatly in the first 30
minutes with blasts mostly coming from Ilie and midfielder Dorinel
Munteanu of German side Cologne.
</P>
<P>
Ilie, who played as forward in the Spanish club up from his
midfielder position in former side Steauna Bucharest, finally found
the net a dozen minutes later, beating two Colombian defenders before
lobbing a ball home near the far post over goalkeeper Farid Mondragon.
</P>
<P>
The Romanians dominated most of the game but Colombia almost
equalized 15 minutes into the second half when striker Freddy Rincon
blasted a 20-meter shot that slided past the left pole.
</P>
<P>
Munteanu and teammates Dan Petrescu and Iulian Filipescu were
warned with yellow cards by Mauritus referee Lim Kee Chong.
</P>
<P>
Jose Santa of Colombia was also cautioned.
</P>
<P>
Romania will face England in their next game on June 22. 
</P>
</TEXT>
