<HEADLINE> French Troops Arrest Bosnian Serb War Crime Suspect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- French troops serving in the NATO
Stabilization Force (SFOR) in Bosnia arrested on Monday morning a
Serb war crime suspect, Milorad Krnojelac, in Foca, southeast
Bosnia, in collaboration with German troops.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted French diplomatic sources in
the NATO headquarters in Brussels as saying that 40 French
commandos took Krnojelac by surprise in the operation carried out
in a zone under the control of French troops serving in the SFOR.
</P>
<P>
Krnojelac, accused of war crimes by the Hague-based
International Tribunal in charge of trying war crime suspects in
former Yugoslavia, was flown to the Netherlands where the tribunal
and a detention center for the war crime suspects are located,
said AFP.
</P>
<P>
The arrest coincided with the opening in Rome of an
international conference on establishing a permanent international
tribunal to judge people accused of genocide, war crimes and crime
against humanity.
</P>
<P>
Over the past one year, France was accused by both the
International Tribunal in the Hague and the United States of
refusing to cooperate in arresting Bosnian Serb war crime
suspects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
