<HEADLINE> Turkey, Kazakhstan Tighten Trade Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Turkey and Kazakhstan have stepped
up their efforts to boost the trade between them, planning to
triple the volume in a decade's time.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev stated here on
Monday that he has ordered to outline such a project to increase
the trade with Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev, who arrived here Sunday evening for a five-day state
visit, made the remark after talks with his Turkish counterpart
Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume between the two countries stood at 267 million
U.S. dollars in 1997 with over 300 Turkish firms operating in the
Central Asian state.
</P>
<P>
Turkish construction firms have undertaken projects worth
nearly 2 billion U.S. dollars and the two parties agreed on
continuing their efforts to encourage Turkish investments in
Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Demirel said that "In the past six years (after
Kazakhstan gained independence), relations between our two
countries have reached such a level that normally could have only
been reached in 30 years."
</P>
<P>
"It is our primary objective to contribute to the
reconstruction and welfare of Kazakhstan," added the Turkish
president.
</P>
<P>
He also called on the Turkish banks to show more interest in
operations in Kazakhstan, saying that a new 300-million-dollar
loan of the Eximbank will be allocated for the country.
</P>
<P>
The two parties also agreed to intensify cooperation in the
fields of oil and natural gas production.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh president is scheduled to meet with Turkish Prime
Minister Mesut Yilmaz on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
