Committee of Nigeria (JACON) in commemorating the fifth
anniversary of the annulled June 12, 1993 election, in which
Moshood Abiola was widely believed to be the winner.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators, numbering a few hundreds, were demanding
the release of Abiola and the end of military rule in Nigeria.
They were dispersed by the police using tear gas. 
