<HEADLINE> Romanian Coach Says Team Deserves Win </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LYON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Romanian coach Anghel Iordanescu said his
team deserved the 1-0 win over Colombia in a group G game here on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
"I am very pleased with how we played, especially as so many of our
players are playing in the World Cup for the first time," said
Iordanescu.
</P>
<P>
He added, "We had very many chances in the frist and were tired in
the second half. But we were pragmatic and intelligent enough to
secure the win."
</P>
<P>
The team's star midfielder Georghe Hagi said he was happy despite
his failure to score.
</P>
<P>
"The important thing is that we won," Hagi said. "Nothing else
matters. We showed that when we needed to be, we are just as good on
defence as on attack."
</P>
<P>
Hagi said it was his last World Cup finals and he would do his best
to leave a good impression. 
</P>
</TEXT>
