<HEADLINE> 2 Major Banks in S. Africa Increase Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Nedcor and Standard Bank
Monday joined other leading South African commercial banks in
raising their lending rates by two percentage points.
</P>
<P>
Absa, Nbs Boland and First National Bank announced last week
that they were hiking their lending rates after the South African
Reserve Bank increased the repo rate.
</P>
<P>
The reserve bank made the move after its intervention on the
exchange market failed to shore up the Rand, which nose-dived to
record lows in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
It had been widely hoped that interest rates could be cut by
two or three percentage points to spur the economy. 
</P>
