<HEADLINE> Ugandan Mayor Detained in US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Hajji Nasser Sebaggala, mayor of
Kampala City in Uganda, has been detained in New York city for
involvement in financial connections, Radio Uganda reported
Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The report said Ugandan Embassy in Washington, United States,
has confirmed the detention of the mayor.
</P>
<P>
Local reports said Sebaggala was held by the U.S. Customs when
he and his wife Sarah Nabagesera were boarding a plane to return
home at about 7:00 p.m. Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
A press release from Ugandan Ministry of Foreign Affairs said
the Ugandan Embassy has already sought and been granted consular
access to Sebaggala in conformity with international laws. The
embassy is extending consular assistance to the mayor and has
enabled him to obtain legal representation, the report added.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, the mayor was to appear in
court on June 15.
</P>
<P>
Sebaggala was returning home from Chicago where he went two
days before to attend an international conference on garbage
collection.
</P>
<P>
He was elected mayor of Kampala city in April in a hotly
contested race in which he defeated four other candidates
although there had been much controversy over his academic
qualifications for the top post of the capital city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
