<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Museveni Satisfied with Gathering of Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has expressed his satisfaction that all the Burundi factions have
come together in the peace talks which opened Monday in Arusha,
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks here after returning from the
all-inclusive peace talks on Burundi, the first of its kind since
a coup that toppled the legitimate government in Burundi in July
1996.
</P>
<P>
In his brief statement, Museveni also challenged all the
Burundi leaders gathered in Arusha to choose a correct turning
point in the political history of their country.
</P>
<P>
Museveni advised the Burundi leaders to consider cleaning the
ideology and the political process in Burundi and take the road
of empowering the Burundians democratically while guaranteeing
security for all.
</P>
<P>
The Burundi leaders should expunge notions of sectarianism and
replace them with notions of Burundism while bearing in mind that
Burundi is among the most ancient countries in Africa, he said.
</P>
<P>
All factions involved in Burundi conflicts were represented at
the opening session which was chaired by former Tanzanian
president Mwalimu Julius Nyerere, who is also the facilitator of
the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Museveni left for the meeting Sunday, accompanied by Ruhakana
Rugunda, the Minister of State for Foreign Affairs in charge of
regional cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
