<HEADLINE> Dutch Coach Writes Letter to FIFA on Kluivert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Dutch coach Guus Hiddink said in Monaco
on Monday that he had written to international soccer body FIFA on the
matter concerning the send-off of Patrick Kluivert.
</P>
<P>
In the letter Hiddink explained the circumstances surrounding
Kluivert's dismissal in their Saturday game against Belgium, he said.
</P>
<P>
But the coach added that the squad must accept the striker's two
match ban.
</P>
<P>
"He's been suspended for two games. It's at least one too many as
there were special circumstances," he said from the team's training
ground in Monaco.
</P>
<P>
FIFA's disciplinary committee said on Sunday that Kluivert, who
received a red card for elbowing Belgian Lorenzo Staelens, would be
banned for two games.
</P>
<P>
Kluivert had said Staelens had provoked him with some abusive
comments and the elbowing was not as serious as it looked. 
