<HEADLINE> E. Africa to Set up Common Legislative Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- James Wapakhabulo, speaker of
Ugandan parliament, announced Monday that arrangements to
establish the East African Legislative Assembly have been
completed.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at the opening of the first regional
workshop on constitutional and public interest law in east Africa
which was held in Entebbe, a city 45 km southwest of Ugandan
capital Kampala, according to a report reaching here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The speaker also said that parliament speakers of the three
east African countries met last week and recommended the
establishment of the assembly which will have power to make laws
in areas identified as east African areas.
</P>
<P>
He commended the foundation for human rights initiative which
organized the workshop and the young generation of lawyers for
doing a better job at bringing east Africa together and creating
human rights awareness.
</P>
<P>
The regional conference is expected to examine current use of
public interest litigation in east Africa and deliberate on
issues of public interest that have been raised by students
involved in litigation. 
</P>
