<HEADLINE> Int'l Conference on Home Science Opens in Kathmandu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A three-day international
conference on "Challenges to Home Science Professionals in
Contributing Toward a Gender Equitable Family/Society in the Next
Millennium" opened here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The conference being attended by 125 home science professionals
from Nepal, India, Pakistan, Bangladesh, the United States, Canada
and Britain will hold extensive discussions on how to make the
home science education effective in the South Asia region, some
participants said.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the conference is to review the home science
education in Nepal, establish linkage particularly with the South
Asian and Southeast Asian countries and identify ways and means to
incorporate gender perspective and concerns in basic-level
education, according to conference sources.
</P>
<P>
The conference organized by the Home Science and Women
Development Association of Nepal was inaugurated by Nepali Queen
Aishwarya.
</P>
<P>
President of the association Lila Devi K.C. said that curricula
on home science, or home activities, should be reviewed and made
effective and skill-oriented and start from the school level.
</P>
</TEXT>
