<HEADLINE> EU Unemployment Rate at 10.2 Per Cent in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate for the
European Union kept at 10.2 percent in the month of April, but it
was 0.5 percent down from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The jobless figure was announced by Eurostat, the
Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the 15-nation union.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate was 11.3 percent for the 11 countries
that are chosen as the founding members of the single currency.
These countries include France, Germany, Belgium, Luxembourg, the
Netherlands, Italy, Spain, Austria, Finland, Ireland and Portugal.
</P>
<P>
With a rate of 2.3 percent, Luxembourg stays lowest among both
EU and Euro 11 countries, followed by Austria with 4.4 percent of
jobless.
</P>
<P>
At the other end of the spectre, Spain topped EU and Euro 11
countries with a jobless rate of 18.8 percent. The next highest
was Finland with 12.6 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
