<HEADLINE> State Bank of Pakistan Announces Austerity Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Governor of the State Bank of
Pakistan (SBP) Muhammad Yaqub has announced austerity measures in
the Central Bank in accordance with the Prime Minister's
directive, the Associated Press of Pakistan reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A meeting held in Karachi Monday was attended by the chief
executives of nationalized commercial banks and the Public Sector
Development Finance Institutions to discuss, among other matters,
measures to implement the National Agenda of Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif in the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
Presiding over the meeting, The Central Bank governor announced
that he decided to vacate the Bank House, the official residence
of SBP Governor, and to move to one of the town houses in regular
staff colony of the Bank shortly.
</P>
<P>
Yaqub has already surrendered one of the two cars officially
provided to him. He and his family have for over a year been using
only one car.
</P>
<P>
Under the new measures, sanctioning limits of Directors and
Chief Managers of the bank have been reduced drastically. No new
construction or alteration activity shall be undertaken, and all
purchase of items of furniture and fixtures have been halted.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, greater economy will be effected in medical
expenditure without compromising the requirements of the
employees. Keeping in view the state of emergency, all decisions
relating to promotions and considerations for grant of additional
benefit to the employees of the bank are temporarily suspended.
</P>
<P>
Yaqub has urged the chief executives of the nationalized
commercial banks to adopt similar austerity measures in their
respective institutions.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif announced in the National Agenda on
June 11 a number of austerity measures in a bid to fight against
the economic sanctions imposed by some western nations in the wake
of Pakistan's detonation of nuclear devices late last month.
</P>
</TEXT>
