<HEADLINE> EU Environment Ministers Near Water Quality Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Environment ministers from
European Union countries on Tuesday unveiled an ambitious plan to
upgrade the water quality within the European Union in a timespan
of 34 years.
</P>
<P>
The ministers, who were able to reach a considerable degree of
consensus that will enable them to finalize a common position,
aimed at drafting a community-wide action plan for the protection
of surface water and groundwater in the 15-nation union.
</P>
<P>
But the environment ministers are still waiting for an opinion
from the European Parliament concerning the water quality issue.
</P>
<P>
All measures to achieve the environmental objectives for a
sustainable protection and use of water will be coordinated and
their effect overseen and monitored within river basins, the
ministers claimed, thus ensuring a coherent and rational way of
water application.
</P>
<P>
The water quality improvement plan in the making was expected
to be designed to provide an overall framework within which the
European Union, national and regional authorities can develop
integrated and coherent water policies and provide measures that
help to identify water issues that are not adequately addressed at
present.
</P>
<P>
But the water quality improvement plan has to cope with river
basin management, actions to combat accidental pollution and a
procedure for the development of coordinated strategies for
dealing with pollution by individual pollutants or groups of
pollutants.
</P>
<P>
The environment ministers admitted that to bring back to good
status the waters of the European Union after generations of
reckless pollution, a gradual step-by-step approach is needed for
inland surface water, transitional waters, coastal waters and
groundwater to be covered.
</P>
<P>
Though the ministers set a five-phase timetable of 34 years for
the implementation and completion of their water quality
improvement plan, some ministers argued that a pollution even
after having the pollution sources under control may take 50 years
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
