<HEADLINE> Experts Suggest Overall Arrangement on Rural Market Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A group of experts who have just
concluded their rural investigation urged the government to make
comprehensive arrangement from the macro point of view on the
development of rural market, which the experts found to have great
potentials.
</P>
<P>
In late May 12 investigation teams were dispatched by the State
Administration of Internal Trade to study the rural market in
different provinces and autonomous regions. Based on their
investigation, experts from these teams held that rational
development of natural, economic and social resources is the key
to developing rural economy and raising rural residents' payable
incomes.
</P>
<P>
They suggest that governments at various levels increase input
in agriculture, scientific and technological development service,
information service and water-conservancy infrastructure, actively
develop high-quality and high-efficiency agriculture, support the
development of enterprises that integrate trade, industry and
agriculture, and expand deep processing of agricultural and the
by-products.
</P>
<P>
The investigation found that the sources of rural residents'
income are increasingly diversified, the income from farming
constitutes only a small part of their total income, and over the
past two years the growth rate of farmers' income was sharply down.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in comparatively developed areas are spending more on
housing, cultural and entertainment activities, means of
communications, education, health-keeping and other aspects, while
farmers in backward areas spend most of their money on necessary
production and living materials.
</P>
<P>
The experts said that rural areas do not have sufficient
infrastructure, which restricts the access of modern consuming
goods to rural market. Efforts should be made to develop rural
public utilities and small towns in a bid to stimulate potential
purchasing power in rural areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
