<HEADLINE> China Bank Promises 850 Million US Dollars of Support to Local Airline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China is expected to
provide 850 million US dollars in financial support to the Xiamen
Airline Co. Ltd in the coming two years.
</P>
<P>
Under a cooperative agreement signed today by the two sides,
the Bank of China will provide all-round financial services and
loan support to the airline company in the next two years, with a
total value of 850 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1984, the Xiamen Airline is the first local
airline company in China. It now boasts 15 Boeing-737s and
Boeing-757s, operates 95 air routes with a total length of more
than 80,000 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Between 1995 and 1997, the Xiamen Airline reported an average
annual growth of 36.48 percent in profits and scored an average
annual profit of 224 million yuan. Its total assets has also
expanded from the original 20 million yuan to the preset 1.14
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Bank of China hailed the agreement as
another important step the bank has taken to help jerk up the
national economy to realize an annual growth of eight percent.
</P>
<P>
In another two efforts to improve lending efficiency through
supporting large and profitable enterprises, the Bank of China has
signed similar agreements with the leading TV-maker the Konka
Group and top PC-maker the Legend Group this year, promising them
loan support worth 4.2 billion yuan and one billion yuan,
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
