<HEADLINE> Egypt, Belarus Agree to Enhance Economic Links </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Belarus and Egypt agreed Tuesday to
set up a joint committee on economic and trade cooperation to
enhance ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
This was reached by Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and
Belarussian President Alexander Lukashenko, who is here on a
two-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting, the two presidents also reached consensus
on giving preferential treatment to each other's companies to
encourage them to launch projects in both countries.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko said Mubarak decided to allow some Belarussian
products to be manufactured in Egypt, which would serve as a
springboard for marketing these items in Africa and the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, Belarus can help in promoting Egyptian exports to the
Commonwealth of Independent States, such as Russia, Ukraine and
Kazakhstan, he said.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko said major Belarussian firms have keen interests in
participating in a giant project being undertaken in Toshka of
Upper Egypt to reclaim thousands of acres of land, as well as in
the Technology Valley project in the Sinai peninsula.
</P>
<P>
"These projects will play a major role in promoting the
competitiveness of Egyptian economy," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Belarussian president singled out certain areas, such as
oil refining, pharmaceuticals, electronics, auto industry and
machinery, as the priorities for both countries to enhance trade
and launch joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
To encourage bilateral trade and joint investment, Egypt and
Belarus also signed Tuesday an agreement on operating a regular
air route between Cairo and Belarussian capital Minsk.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko arrived in Cairo Monday on a two-day visit, his
first since the two countries established diplomatic ties in
1994. He was accompanied by a large delegation of ministers and
leading businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Belarus is having a major surplus in its trade with Egypt,
which stood at 54 million U.S. dollars last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
