<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain Disrupts Hunan Rail Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Continuous heavy rain that has
battered central and northern Hunan Province since Monday has
disrupted traffic on the Zhicheng-Liuzhou railway. Two sections of
the Beijing-Guangzhou railway in the province have imposed speed
limits.
</P>
<P>
The torrential rain began on Monday evening and triggered off
mountain torrents which damaged the northern part of the
Zhicheng-Liuzhou railway line and forced it to close at 3
a.m. today.
</P>
<P>
Trains traveling on the Beijing-Guangzhou railway had to reduce
their speed to 45 kph due to some damages to the line.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government is busy with rescue work, and the
local transportation department has sent workers to repair the
damaged roads and railways.
</P>
<P>
According to local weather forecast, the heavy rain will
continue through June 19, and after a respite for one or two days,
the province is expected to have another wet spell.  
</P>
</TEXT>
