<HEADLINE> New Mobile Phone Network in Trial Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The new CDMA mobile phone network
-- the Shanghai Great Wall Network -- opened today for trial
operation in this east China metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The network, with a frequency of 800 mega-hertz, was jointly
built by the Shanghai Posts and Telecommunications Bureau and the
Nanjing Military Area Command. It is expected to further enlarge
the local mobile transmission capacity and improve the quality of
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
An exchange center and 67 base stations have been built,
covering the whole metropolitan area.
</P>
<P>
CDMA (code diversion multiple access), the most advanced
telecommunication technology in the world, provides clearer
transmission, and better security. 
</P>
