<HEADLINE> Police Ready for Opening of Hong Kong New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The police station at the Chek
Lap Kok new airport is operating in full strength three weeks
before the airport opens for business.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong Police spokesman said here Tuesday the Chek Lap Kok
police station is now running at full capacity with all its 397
members in position, including 335 police officers and 62 civilian
staff. The station had only 88 policemen when it came into
operation in September last year.
</P>
<P>
Officers newly deployed to the station will familiarize
themselves with the 1,248-ha Chek Lap Kok platform by patrolling
the area, and visit various institutions and companies there,
according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"In addition, training on aviation security legislation,
overall airport operations, aircraft accident drills and counter
terrorist action will be strengthened," he said.
</P>
<P>
For the next three weeks, the Chek Lap Kok police station will
be fully operational in parallel with the Kai Tak police station,
which will be closed on July 6.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that police are confident to maintain
effective policing and public order at the new airport as they do
at Kai Tak.  
</P>
