<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exhibition Highlights Chinese Lawyers (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- China, the world's most populous
country, now has 100,000 lawyers, compared with only 212 when it
began its reform and opening-up in the lawyers system 19 years ago.
</P>
<P>
This is one of the statistics revealed at an exhibition which
opened here today. The exhibition, titled "Chinese Lawyers in the
Tide of Reform and Opening-Up", is the first of its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
According to the exhibition, the total number of law firms in
China is now more than 8,300, from only 79 two decades ago.
</P>
<P>
"Lawyers and the lawyers system are not part of the Chinese
judicial tradition; they did not emerge in China until less than a
century ago," said Wang Li, a senior local lawyer.
</P>
<P>
However, she said, "the reform and opening-up has brought
springtime for Chinese lawyers.
</P>
<P>
"You may not know how many lawyers there are among the crowds
rushing to their offices in the morning, but the role played by
lawyers is now increasing dramatically," she said.
</P>
<P>
More than 11,000 Chinese families or individual citizens have
hired private lawyers so far, according to the exhibition -- and
the figure is expected to be doubled very soon.
</P>
<P>
"In the near future most Chinese will find that lawyers are
important in their lives, not only because they can help them win
court cases, but also because lawyers can help them avoid disputes
and help them earn more money," an expert from the All China
Lawyers Association said.
</P>
<P>
High-speed economic growth in China in recent years has
involved not only a number of large- and medium-scale construction
projects but also more and more foreign-related economic
activities. This is another area in which Chinese lawyers have
made great contributions.
</P>
<P>
According to the exhibition, in the largest Chinese industrial
city of Shanghai, lawyers have participated in more than 250
large- and medium-scale construction projects since 1993,
contributing much to the smooth operation of the bidding,
financing and contract negotiation of these projects.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980616.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exhibition Highlights Chinese Lawyers (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1997 Chinese lawyers handled more than 25,000
foreign-related economic cases, provided consultancy services to
more than 1,200 overseas-invested projects.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing lawyers handled more than 100 financial cases last
year, involving over 10 billion yuan (about 1.25 billion US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, according to experts, the lack of high-quality lawyers
who can deal properly with cases in some areas of speciality like
finance, securities and real estate is still a problem.
</P>
<P>
At present, only some 1,600 lawyers nationwide can handle cases
involving securities. These lawyers are concentrated in about 300
law firms.
</P>
<P>
According to the exhibition, about 11,000 government
departments and 118,000 enterprises have hired lawyers.
</P>
<P>
To suit the needs of those who can not afford the charges for
various reasons, China has so far set up 170 legal aid centers
which have handled more than 70,000 cases gratis or at reduced
fees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
