<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Strengthen Pharmaceuticals Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- China's pharmaceuticals
supervision authority has vowed to keep a close eye on the
nation's massive drug market in a bid to ensure the safe use of
medicines.
</P>
<P>
The newly-established State Bureau of Pharmaceuticals
Supervision and Management announced today that it will "enhance
technological supervision and administration of the research,
production, marketing and use of drugs".
</P>
<P>
The authority has the responsibility to draft rules related to
drugs administration, publish official drugs standards and decide
the catalogue of national essential drugs.
</P>
<P>
Registration of new drugs, generic drugs, imported drugs and
traditional Chinese medicines are also to be undertaken by the
bureau. In addition, it will conduct clinical research into drugs
and monitor adverse reactions.
</P>
<P>
Control of pharmaceuticals advertising, narcotics, toxic
drugs, psychotropic drugs, radio-pharmaceuticals and some special
medical instruments will be tightened.
</P>
<P>
A national report on examinations of medicine quality will be
published regularly, the bureau said, while pledging to crack down
upon production and sales of fake and shoddy products.
</P>
<P>
The authority plans to introduce a system of OTC (over the
counter) drugs across the country, as well as a certification
scheme for pharmacists.
</P>
<P>
The bureau and its workers must work under a "scientific, fair,
efficient, honest and clean" system in order to ensure that the
1.2 billion Chinese people use safe medicines, said Zheng Xiaoyu,
director of the bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau was established early this year as a result of the
Chinese government's efforts to streamline redundant governmental
organizations.
</P>
<P>
It replaced the former State Pharmaceuticals Administration, the
State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine and a
pharmaceuticals administration department under the Ministry of
Health.  
</P>
</TEXT>
