<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Provinces Warned Of Dangers of La Nina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's National Search and
Rescue Agency Tuesday warned the country's provinces against the
threats of abnormal weather phenomenon "La Nina," which may bring
heavy rains with high precipitation in November or December.
</P>
<P>
"Each province and regency should anticipate the impact of high
precipitation from now on, including possible floods in the next
six months," chief of the agency Harianto was quoted by Antara
News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Although the Meteorological and Geophysical Agency has yet to
issue information on the dangers of high precipitation, all areas
should take measures to deal with it, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should learn from the impact of last year's El Nino. As a
consequence of the prolonged drought, the condition of our forests
and farmlands became a cause for major concern," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
