<HEADLINE> Malaysia Approves 372 Manufacturing Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia approved 372
manufacturing projects with total proposed capital investments of
13.887 billion ringgit (about 3.463 billion U.S. dollars) from
January to May this year.
</P>
<P>
Its Minister of International Trade and Industry Rafidah
disclosed here Tuesday that of the total number of projects, 194
were for expansion or diversification purposes.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investments made up 39.5 percent of the total
investments while local investments made up the rest, she said in
her speech at the annual luncheon of the Malaysian International
Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
"This is in line with the government's objective to achieve a
60:40 local-foreign investment ratio in the country," she added.
</P>
<P>
The biggest investors during the five-month period were the
Americans with 2.504 billion ringgit (about 0.624 billion U.S.
dollars) followed by the Japanese 1.363 billion ringgit (about
0.339 billion dollars), Rafidah said.
</P>
<P>
She said that there were 24 projects with capital investments
of 100 million ringgit (about 25 million dollars) and above each.
The total capital investments in the 24 projects amounted to
10.490 billion ringgit (about 2.62 billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
