<HEADLINE> Canada to Join NATO Military Exercises Near Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Canadian warplanes will join the
NATO's military exercises near Kosovo, the Globe and Mail
newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The deployment of Canadian warplanes, which were absent from
NATO's initial show of force near Kosovo Monday, was approved by
the cabinet on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Six Canadian CF-18s are expected to be shepherded across the
Atlantic to the Aviano airbase in Italy by a U.S. Air Force KC-10
tanker either late Thursday or early Friday.
</P>
<P>
Canadian air crews and ground-support personnel have all
received orders and those based elsewhere are already gathering at
the airbase near Bagotville, Quebec. 
</P>
</TEXT>
