<HEADLINE> Work to Start on New Guangzhou Airport at Year End </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- This capital of Guangdong
Province in south China will start to build a new international
airport at the end of this year to cater to the growing demands of
aviation.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 18.9 billion yuan (about 2.33 billion US
dollars), the new airport will cover a total area of 16 sq km. The
first phase of construction, designed to be completed in three
years, includes building two 3,800-meter-long, 60-meter-wide
runways, a terminal building with a floor space of 280,000 sq m
and a parking apron for 72 aircraft.
</P>
<P>
In connection with the construction of this airport and with
another 25 airports which are to be updated and expanded in eastern
China, the Guangdong branch of the China Council for the Promotion
of International Trade and a Hong Kong international exhibition
company will jointly stage an exhibition of airport equipment in
Guangzhou in late November.
</P>
<P>
Airport equipment manufacturers from a dozen countries
including the United States, the Great Britain, Germany, France
and Japan will attend the exhibition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
