<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to fall
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index (STII) shed 3.88 points to close at 1,048.96 points on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, share prices recovered from sharp early losses to
close slightly lower.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said market sentiment was weak under pressure from
volatile currencies and rising interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Heavy selling of property counters, seen most vulnerable to
rising rates, pulled the property index down to a new year-low
before it rebounded slightly.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 148.48 million units,
valued at 270.34 million Singapore dollars (about 155.37 million
U.S. dollars). There were 81 rises against 232 falls while 275
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
DBS Land was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 15.12 million units. It was followed by OUB F which
had 8.38 million shares traded. Informat was next with 6.44
million shares changing hands.
</P>
<P>
F&AMP;N, KepCorp and SingTel 100 were the top three on the gainers
list of the day as they rose by 0.06 cents respectively. F&AMP;N
finished at 4.20 Singapore dollars. KepCorp ended at 2.49
Singapore dollars while SingTel 100 closed at 2.19 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it fell
by 2.90 Singapore dollars to end at 18.60 Singapore dollars.
CityDev w98 lost 77 cents and closed at 1.01 Singapore dollars.
Bukit Sem was next which shed 40 cents to finish at 8.00 Singapore
dollars. 
</P>
