<BODY>
<HEADLINE> COMESA Moves to Expand Capital Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) has started to expand the capital base
of its PTA Bank to facilitate the economic reforms currently
conducted by most member countries.
</P>
<P>
PTA Bank President Martin Ogang said here Tuesday that the
capital base will be expanded from the current 400 million U.S.
Dollars to more than five billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the African Development Bank, the PTA Bank will focus
on making the private sector an engine for economic development in
Africa, said Ogang.
</P>
<P>
The bank president said that the bank's lending capacity to
the member states will be raised when the expansion process is
completed by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
After the expansion process, the bank will be able to lend up
to 300 million U.S. Dollars annually to the members, he said.
</P>
<P>
The bank has lent over 100 million U.S. Dollars to Zambia for
various development projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
