He said that it is a miracle that the northern district, where
live a great North African community, had not been put in flame.
</P>
<P>
Gaudin said that he regretted that after the primary incidents
took place on Sunday night, Marseille did not give a image as a
"city under siege."
</P>
<P>
"I told Dominique Baudis (mayor of Toulouse) and the
Toulousians who will host the next match of English: You should
criss-cross the town and take initiatives," he said.
</P>
<P>
