<HEADLINE> Cave Rescue Girl Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- One of the two teenage girls who
were rescued after being trapped for 42 days in a cave in Guizhou
Province died here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Liang Xiaofei, 19, was rescued last Saturday together
with her classmate, Li Qingzhu, who is still in danger, said the
doctor responsible for their medical treatment, adding that Li is
now extremely weak physically and suffers from acidosis and a lung
infection.
</P>
<P>
Li is being treated with doses of albumin and antibiotics,
according to the doctor.
</P>
<P>
A party of four explorers stumbled on the girls, and found that
their companions Huang Yan and a boy named Wang Shunrong, had
already died of starvation.
</P>
<P>
The four entered the cave May 2, not having informed anyone of
where they were going, and got lost when their candles went out.
</P>
<P>
Their schools reported them missing seven days later. 
