<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Family Planning Policy of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman
Zhu Bangzao pointed out that China has a dual responsibility --
toward its own people and the people of the rest of the world --
to maintain its family planning policy.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a regular press conference here today
while commenting on an attack from overseas on China's family
planning policy.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the issue of population is of strategic
significance in today's world, and China, with 1.2 billion
population and an annual increase of 1.3 million, has taken family
planning as a basic State policy.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Chinese government will, together with
the international community, contribute to stabilizing the global
population growth while developing the country's economy and
improving the living standards of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government has always opposed any form
of force when carrying out the family planning policy.
</P>
<P>
``We will promptly correct any wrongdoing in implementing the
family planning policy, but simultaneously oppose any action to
distort our family planning policy and politicize the issue of
family planning,'' he noted. 
</P>
