Belarus has expressed its desire to join the Non-Aligned
Movement and to exchange visits with Egypt on a technical level,
Moussa said after the signing of the agreements.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko and Mubarak have held two rounds of talks on
regional and international issues of mutual concern, the latest
developments in the Mideast peace process, as well as enhancing
bilateral ties, especially in economy, trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko's visit is his first to Egypt since the two
countries established diplomatic ties in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Belarus is the most developed of the Commonwealth of
Independent States in the field of industry.
</P>
<P>
Trade exchange between the two countries stood at 63 million
U.S. dollars last year, with 3 million dollars of Egyptian exports
to Belarus and nearly 60 million dollars of Egyptian imports from
Belarus. 
