<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 alumni of the
Whampoa Military Academy from Beijing, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macao
and other parts of the country today gathered in the Sun Yat-sen
Memorial Hall here to mark the 10th anniversary of the Beijing
Municipal Association of the Alumni of the Whampoa Military
Academy.
</P>
<P>
In the past ten years, the Beijing association has extended its
connections with Whampoa alumni both at home and overseas,
actively promoted the principle of "one country, two systems," and
contributed a great deal to the peaceful reunification of the
country.
</P>
<P>
It has received more than 1,400 Whampoa alumni from at home and
overseas, and 11,000 letters and congratulatory cards from them,
while introducing funds worth more than 500 million yuan (about 60
million US dollars) since its establishment.
</P>
<P>
At today's celebration meeting, the participants approved an
open letter to all Whampoa alumni in Taiwan, calling on them to
follow the patriotic spirit of Whampoa and make concerted efforts
to promote peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
The Whampoa Military Academy was established in 1924 by Dr.Sun
Yat-sen, forerunner of the Chinese democratic revolution. 
