<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Tuesday on continued
selling pressure as investors' confidence was undermined by the
weak Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The market staged a mild technical rebound in mid-morning but
fell further in the afternoon as worries about economic prospects
in the region took dominance.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100 quality stock Composite Index fell 3.63
percent or 16.4 points to 435.84, the all-share Emas Index slipped
4.02 points to 113.82, the Industrial Index dropped 37.5 points to
878 and the Second Board index shed 1.31 points to 102.85.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 488 to 128 while 151 counters were
unchanged, 152 untraded and 22 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 133.820 million shares valued
at 292.628 million ringgit (about 72.974 million U.S. dollars)
from 108.059 million shares valued at 232.654 million ringgit
(about 58.018 million dollars) traded on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the main board rose to 127.587 million shares valued
at 284.106 million ringgit (about 70.849 million dollars) from
Monday's 102.272 million shares worth 224.866 million ringgit
(about 56.076 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the second board, turnover increased to 6.233 million valued
at 8.521 million ringgit (about 2.124 million dollars) from 5.787
million shares valued at 7.787 million ringgit (about 1.941
million dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals were almost unchanged at 4.23 million valued
at 13.449 million ringgit (about 3.353 million dollars) compared
to 4.238 million shares worth 12.078 million ringgit (about 3.011
million dollars) on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
