<HEADLINE> Albania Congratulates NATO Air Exercises Near Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Albania Monday congratulated the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) on its air exercises
conducted in Albanian air space near Kosovo Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued Monday evening, the Albanian government
said NATO's air exercises indicated the common aspiration of the
international community, in particular NATO member countries, not
to allow Kosovo becoming a second Bosnia-Herzegovina, according to
local media Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement said if diplomatic efforts turn out to be
unsuccessful, NATO should use its good offices to resolve the
Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Swedish Defense Minister Bjorn Von Sydov Monday
evening, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano said that Albania was
ready to make all logistics facilities available to the NATO
exercises.
</P>
<P>
Over 80 warplanes from 13 of the 16 NATO countries Monday
morning took part in the air exercises in Albanian and Macedonian
air spaces adjacent to Kosovo, aimed at exerting pressure on the
Yugoslav government to halt the violence in kosovo, a Yugoslavian
province with an ethnic Albanian majority.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 people have been killed and some 65,000 people
become refugees since the Serb-led government of the Yugoslav
federation began "a military crackdown" on ethnic Albanians'
independence movement in Kosovo early this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
