<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Slightly Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rebounded 63.95
points, or 0.86 percent to close at 7,526.45 points on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index recovered some of the losses it
suffered on Monday when it closed at 7,462.5 points, a three-year
low caused by rising local interbank rates and increasing pressure
from the weakening Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover was 7.574 billion HK dollars (971
million U.S. dollars), 1.335 billion HK dollars (171 million
U.S. dollars) more than that of Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index gained 24.86 points, or 0.33 percent, to
open at 7,487.36 Tuesday morning. It rose 105.8 points, or 1.42
percent, to close at 7,568.3 at midday.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong shares plunged 452.94 points and was 5.72 percent
lower than last Friday's closing figure. 
</P>
