<HEADLINE> Military Reshuffle: A Result of Massacre </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
has sent army Chief of Staff Brig. James Kazini to temporarily
replace Col. Charles Angina as Commander of the second division
fighting the rebels in the west.
</P>
<P>
This decision was made by Museveni, also the
commander-in-chief of the armed forces, in response to a loud
outcry against the army's tactics in the June 8 massacre in which
over 80 students were burnt to death by Allied Democratic Forces
(ADF) rebels in a pre-dawn inferno.
</P>
<P>
A Tuesday Monitor report said Deputy Army Commander, Brig.
Joram Mugume, will serve in Kazini's former position as acting
Chief of Staff.
</P>
<P>
Mugume was quoted by Tuesday's New Vision daily as saying that
Angina is to go for studies. But he did not reveal the fate of
Angina's deputy, who he said was also replaced in this shakeup.
</P>
<P>
On the early morning of June 8, some 200 ADF rebels mounted a
surprise attack on the Kichwamba Technical Institute in western
Kabarole District. They burnt three student dormitories and
abducted over 100 students.
</P>
<P>
The government army protecting the college was reported to
have fled for their life without staging any resistance.
</P>
<P>
This massacre quickly gripped the attention of the whole
country and the government has been blamed by the locals and the
bereaved families.
</P>
<P>
Following the massacre, hundreds of residents of the districts
of Kasese, Kabarole and Bundibugyo started deserting their homes
on June 10 for sake of safety.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, parents of Mitandi Adventist College in Kabarole
have withdrawn their children fearing a similar blood bath.
</P>
<P>
Lt. Nasur Kibirige, the second division spokesman, said :"
there is panic in the three districts that something horrific
might happen again."
</P>
<P>
He attributed the rebel attack to the mounting pressure
exerted on them by the government army and their defeat in the
battle.
</P>
<P>
An officer in Bombo said this reshuffle is meant to inject
more vigor in the war against the ADF rebels.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
