<DOCNO> XIE19980616.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Judicial Police Mission Starts Visit to Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A Macao judicial police delegation
left here for Beijing on Tuesday to start a three-day official
visit to discuss anti-crime cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Led by Antonio Baptista, director of the Macao Judicial Police
Department, the delegation is paying the visit at the invitation
of Interpol National Central Bureau of China, said a press release
from the Macao Government Information Office on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the visit is to enhance cooperation between
Macao and China's mainland so that the fight against organized
crimes and drug smuggling will be carried out more effectively.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Beijing, the delegation members will meet
and hold talks with the director of the Interpol National Central
Bureau of China.
</P>
<P>
In addition, they will visit Guangzhou, capital of South
China's Guangdong Province, to hold a joint meeting with security
officers of the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
