The Paris police department said that several hundred German
fans considered to be potentially dangerous and a group of other
German fans without tickets showed up outside the stadium
unexpectedly before the match began.
</P>
<P>
In order to contain the wave of fans, 1,500 policemen were
deployed around the stadium, said the police department.
</P>
<P>
They questioned whoever dared to break the police control line
or damage vehicles, it said. 
