<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Access to electricity in Zimbabwe,
with a population of about 12.5 million people, still remains low
with more than 70 percent of the population still living under
conditions without electricity, a senior government official said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Director of energy within the Ministry of Transport and Energy
Cornelius Muzezewa said this problem called for an aggressive
collaborative program between the country's power utility and the
government to connect more consumers, especially in the rural
areas where two thirds of the population are living.
</P>
<P>
