opened here on Monday to review regional power policies and to
map out strategies on how to attract investment into this sector.
</P>
<P>
He said between 20 and 28 percent of the country's population
have access to electricity with 4.62 percent in the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed the government's policy to amend the Electricity
Act in order to introduce a regulator for the electricity
industry and introduce independent power producers at generation
level. 
