<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bottled Water No Better than Tap Water: HK Consumer Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Bottled water is not that much
better than tap water, according to a report on a recent test of
30 brands on sale on the Hong Kong market, which was carried out
by Hong Kong's Consumer Council.
</P>
<P>
The report said that most bottled water did not possess any
greater health properties and might even contain more impurities.
</P>
<P>
Some samples of bottled water contained higher levels of
undesirable chemicals such as arsenic and lead, than samples of
tap water taken from various sources in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Harmful chemicals were found in 23 samples, although the levels
complied with Hong Kong's Food Adulteration (Metallic
Contamination) Regulations.
</P>
<P>
Some samples were found to be slightly too acidic (less than pH
6) and might worsen the health of people suffering from kidney
disease. Such patients might be more susceptible to kidney
stones, caused by an increase of urea in the body fluids.
</P>
<P>
"If a consumer is looking for mineral content, they can
definitely consume tap water instead of paying for bottled water,"
Lo Chi-kin, publicity and community relations committee
chairperson, was quoted by English-language newspaper Hong Kong
Standard as saying.
</P>
<P>
But it was their choice if the consumer was after style, image
or labels. The best approach to absorb minerals was through a
balanced diet, Lo added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980616.0168 </DOCNO>
