<HEADLINE> China Concerned Over Australian Party's Anti-Asia Racism Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- China's Foregin Ministry spokesman
Zhu Bangzao today expresses his concern over the Australian One
Nation Party's anti-Asia and national racism policy.
</P>
<P>
The One Nation Party reportedly secured 23 percent of the
vote in conservative Queensland State Saturday. Although election
of the state is a domestic affair of Australia, China is still
deeply concerned with the recent anti-Asia racism remarks
made by the party, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Australia is a multi-cultural society where
overseas Chinese and immigrants from other Asian countries or
regions have made great contributions to its economic development
and social progress.
</P>
<P>
At a time when ethnic equality has become the current global
trend, the One Nation Party's anti-Asia and national racism
policy will not only be unpopular but will also run against
historical trends, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
