<DOCNO> XIE19980616.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vogts not Satisfied with Germany's Performance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- German coach Berti Vogts was not fully
satisfied with his European champion team's performance in their 2-0
win here over the United States in the World Cup finals on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Germany scored one goal in the each half to clinch the victory in
Group F but Vogts said the overall performance from the European
champion was not good enough.
</P>
<P>
"It was important to get the three points, of course, and we did
start well," Vogts said. "But then we lost our way."
</P>
<P>
He added, "A 2-0 win is a reasonable result. But we lost our shape
and gave thenm a sniff of getting something out of the game by giving
them a few chances. Andrea Kopke was excellent in goal, thank
goodness, to ensure we kept a clean sheet."
</P>
<P>
Vogts added, "We need to find a better rhythm and close our
opponents down more," Vogts said. "A lot of passes went astray, and
you will get punished for that at this level. We have a tough game
against Yugoslavia coming up, and we have to pull our socks up for
that one."
</P>
<P>
German will meet Yugoslavia in Lens on June 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
