<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Sichuan-Yunnan Railway Under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Construction of a new railway
which will link Sichuan and Yunnan provinces commenced today in
the the latter.
</P>
<P>
Work on the Sichuan section of the railway started four days
earlier in the former.
</P>
<P>
The Neikun Railway will link the Sichuan city of Neijiang with
Kunming, capital of Yunnan Province. The 871-kilometer line will
be constructed at a cost of 11 billion yuan and is scheduled for
completion in 2002.
</P>
<P>
The north-south railway will provide more convenient links with
southwest China and is expected to alleviate poverty in many areas
along the route. The railway will also cut the distance between
Sichuan and Fangcheng Port in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
