<HEADLINE> ADB to Provide Assistance Grant to Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
will provide a technical assistance grant of 1.5 million U.S.
dollars to Sri Lanka for a water resources management project, the
Manila-based bank said in a press release Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The grant will help promote efficient investments in priority
subprojects for water supply management, flood control, water
quality control and watershed management in five river basins near
Colombo.
</P>
<P>
It would also help restore economically important wetland and
lake ecosystems in the area, the ADB said. 
