<HEADLINE> High-Tech Firms Enlivening China's Old Industrial Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 16 (Xinhua) -- High-tech firms of information
technology, new materials and biological engineering are
mushrooming in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
An old leading industrial base of China, Liaoning is confronted
with difficulties in economic develoment due to poor operation of
a large number of its state-owned enterprises in recent years.
</P>
<P>
So, the provincial government has begun to take measures to
develop the high-tech industry in a bid to rejuvenate the
debt-ridden state sector.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Science and Technology Commission of Liaoning
said that the information industry has witnessed the fastest
increase over the past few years, and it achieved an output value
of 55 billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Lianyou Group and Dongjiang Group, two developers of software
and IC cards, have grown into giants in producing related
communication products.
</P>
<P>
Also a leading software developer, East Software Group is
involved in research on medical apparatus and instruments, and has
succeeded in producing CT, making China the world's fifth country
to be able to manufacture the medical equipment.
</P>
<P>
As a result, high-tech industries such as new materials,
biological engineering, and pharmaceutical bases are taking shape,
with more and more new products making their debut on the market,
boosting local economic growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
