<HEADLINE> Mubarak Meets With Belarussian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
Tuesday morning held a tete-a-tete meeting with Belarussian
President Alexandr Lukashenko who arrived here Monday on his first
visit to Egypt, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Their talks dealt with regional and international issues of
mutual concern, the latest developments in the Mideast peace
process, as well as enhancing bilateral ties, especially in
economy, trade and investment.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders held their first session of talks Monday night.
</P>
<P>
During his two-day visit, Lukashenko is accompanied by
ministers of foreign affairs, economy, industry and agriculture
and a big delegation of businessmen.
</P>
<P>
He is due to meet with Egyptian businessmen later Tuesday to
discuss prospects for activating economic and trade ties between
the two countries, including the establishment of joint projects.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are expected to sign a package of agreements
covering trade, air transport, elimination of dual taxation,
higher education and health.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko's visit is his first to Egypt since the two
countries established diplomatic ties in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Belarus is the most developed of the Commonwealth of
Independent States in the field of industry.
</P>
<P>
Trade exchange between the two countries stood at 63 million
U.S. dollars last year, with 3 million dollars of Egyptian exports
to Belarus and nearly 60 million dollars of Egyptian imports from
Belarus.
</P>
<P>
Belarussian Foreign Minister Ivan Antonovich visited Egypt in
January and signed two agreements on encouraging foreign
investments in the two countries and promoting bilateral economic
and technical links. 
</P>
</TEXT>
