<HEADLINE> Fee-free Policy Adopted in Chinese Development Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Heyuan city of south China's
Guangdong Province initiated a fee-free policy to attract
investors to its development zone.
</P>
<P>
Any foreign entrepreneur who opens a business in the Mingzhu
Development Zone will as of June only be charged with related
taxes but not fees, a local government official said.
</P>
<P>
This is the city's latest effort to encourage overseas
investment, which has been slow to come due to poor services and
various kinds of randomly collecting fees.
</P>
<P>
The city set up a special office last year to straighten out
the malpractices, and opened a complaint hotline to the public,
providing round-the-clock services.
</P>
<P>
It has also decided to keep the highest price of electricity
for industrial use in the zone below 0.7 yuan per kwh within five
years, and price hikes will be lower than the provincial average
level after that. 
</P>
</TEXT>
