<HEADLINE> AON Risk Services Group Reinvests in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- AON Risk Services Group, the
biggest broking company in the world, has reinvested in Zambia
after three decades break, Zambia Daily Mail reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The local newspaper quoted David Birch, one of the company's
directors, as saying in Kitwe, northern Zambia, that the company
has also acquired risk consultancy and insurance broking in
Botswana, Kenya, Lesotho, Malawi, South Africa, Swaziland,
Tanzania, Uganda and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
During the launch of MINET he said the U.S.-based company is
devoting a lot of time, money and resources to its African
operations.
</P>
<P>
An AON Africa regional committee is likely to be set up to
enhance high levels of professionalism in the region, according
to him.
</P>
<P>
Kitwe mayor William Nyirenda welcomed the company and assured
investors that 40.9 kilometres of the road network will be
rehabilitated through the world bank while the National Roads
Board will take care of another 50 kilometres in the area.
</P>
<P>
Nyirenda said his city council is determined to facilitate an
environment friendly city and urged stake holders to be conscious
of hazards. 
</P>
