<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Improves Supervision over Commercial Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC),
the central bank, issued a circular today calling for strict
supervision over commercial banks in order to avoid financial
risks and improve internal controls and the quality of management.
</P>
<P>
The circular instructed all commercial banks to strictly abide
by the Commercial Bank Law and the General Rule on Bank Loans when
extending loans. Urban commercial banks were also urged to ensure
that their loan programs give priority to local small- and
medium-sized enterprises and reemployment projects.
</P>
<P>
The circular also stipulated that funds belonging to
commercial banks are subject to the centralized management of
their respective headquarters operations.
</P>
<P>
Urban commercial banks with the ratio of their capital funds
less than eight percent or the ratio of bad loans exceeding 30
percent of their total assets may not distribute cash dividends to
shareholders.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC urged all commercial banks to verify assets, reduce
bad loans and increase their payment ability.
</P>
<P>
The circular also contained detailed provisions covering
financial and personnel management, organizational systems and
other aspects of operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
