<HEADLINE> Italy Prepare to Face Cameroon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Italy prepare to face their second
group opponents Cameroon on Wednesday saying they know little about
the Cameroon team.
</P>
<P>
Just one day before the Group B match in Montpellier, Italian
head coach Cesare Maldini still keeps his game plan a secret.
</P>
<P>
Even Italian captain Paolo Maldini, son of the head coach, said
he had no idea whether his father will stick with the two-man attack
used in their match against Chile or throw on an extra striker in an
all-out bid for victory.
</P>
<P>
"We still don't know who will play or what the formation will
be," said Paolo Maldini, "My dad has changed the team around before,
but I honestly don't know what his plan is this time."
</P>
<P>
Christian Veri agreed with Paolo:"I don't know what the coach
will decide or who will play against Cameroon. We've practised with
three strikers in training over the past few days and I think it's
worked okay."
</P>
<P>
The Italians are conscious of the strength of the Indomitable
Lions who failed to win three points against Austria due to bad luck.
</P>
<P>
"Physically they're a very strong team," said Cesare Maldini
said. "And I think they have improved a lot technically under Le Roy."
</P>
</TEXT>
