<HEADLINE> Yellow River Power Station Goes Online </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Daxia Hydropower Station
entered operations today on the Yellow River, China's
second longest river.
</P>
<P>
The station, located 65 kilometers northeast of Lanzhou,
capital of Gansu Province, is equipped with four 75,000-kw and one
24,500-kw generating units. It was also designed to aid
irrigation and navigation activities.
</P>
<P>
Daxia, a key project listed in China's Eighth Five-Year Plan
(1991-95), is expected to ease electricity shortages in Gansu
Province and northwest China as a whole. 
</P>
</TEXT>
