<HEADLINE> Philippine Jobless Rate Hits 13.3 Percent in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' unemployment
situation got worse in April with the jobless rate soaring to 13.3
percent, the highest in the past seven years, the National
Statistics Office said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The office said that in the period, employment in industry and
services went up by 1.4 and 7.1 percent respectively. However,
total employment fell because of the losses in unpaid family
workers and own-account workers mainly in the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
By region, Metro Manila posted the highest unemployment rate of
18.9 percent, the National Statistics Office said.
</P>
<P>
Due to El Nino and the Asian financial crisis, the Philippines'
agriculture saw negative growth in the first quarter this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
