<HEADLINE> Vietnam Starts Trial of 10 Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Ten alleged drug traffickers were
brought to a five-day trial in Vietnam's central province of Ha
Tinh on Tuesday, the Vietnam News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The 10 drug traffickers -- six Laotians and four Vietnamese,
allegedly brought 51.72 kilograms of heroin from Laos into Vietnam
in 1996 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
They were arrested by Vietnamese police in April last year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's biggest known drug syndicate was exposed in Hanoi two
years ago when 18 Vietnamese and two Laotians confessed to
smuggling as many as 224 kilograms of heroin into Vietnam since
1992.
</P>
<P>
Besides, seven of 20 former police officers, border guards,
truck drivers and traders involved in drug trafficking
were executed early this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
