<HEADLINE> Nairobi Ranks World's 18th Most-Expensive City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Nairobi, the Kenyan capital, is
the 18th most-expensive city in the world, a survey released by
an international real estate firm says.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's Daily Nation newspaper Tuesday quoted the survey by
the Corcoran Group, one of the largest real estates firms
worldwide, as reporting.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. company bases its assessment of cities on the sale
price of the most expensive two-bedroom apartments.
</P>
<P>
The survey says that a two-bedroom apartment in Nairobi, with
an average size of 1,600 square feet, costs 2.5 million Shillings
or 400,000 U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The survey ranks London as the most expensive city, with a
two-bedroom apartment costing 1.4 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is second, with a similar apartment costing 1.32
million Dollars, while Paris is placed third at 1.31 million
Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The only other African country among the first 25 most
expensive countries is South Africa which is ranked eight with an
average price of 754,000 Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Corcoran Group is based in Manhattan, New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
