<HEADLINE> Vietnam Reports Slowdown in Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam is suffering a slowdown in
economic growth this year as its exports face fierce competition
on a narrower international market, Tuesday's edition of Vietnam
News quoted Prime Minister Phan Van Khai as saying.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate of the gross domestic product (GDP) for the
first five months of this year dropped to 6.8 percent from 9.1
percent for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
