mid-term review by the Donor Consultative Group, a mix of the
World Bank, Asian Development Bank, donor countries and
non-government organizations.
</P>
<P>
Citing export difficulties as a major cause for the slowdown,
Khai warned that "these negative factors have affected the
nation's macro-economic balance and would do so for years to come".
</P>
<P>
He urged international donors to continue financial support for
Vietnam, while promising that his government would speed up the
renovation process, despite hardships, and seek to improve the
investment and business environment for foreign and domestic
enterprises. 
