<HEADLINE> Two Major Drug Dealers Arrested in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE BOGOTA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Colombian police captured
two major drug dealers in the capital city of Santafe Bogota on
Sunday, the national radio reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jose Carmen Galeano and his younger brother Melecio, accused of
being leading members of the East Colombia drug group, had been
wanted by police since November 1996.
</P>
<P>
The police said Jose Carmen was responsible for providing
chemical material used in processing cocaine in Meta and Vichada,
while Melecio oversaw the manufacture of the drug and its sale,
mainly to the United States.
</P>
<P>
The well-organized drug group was formed as the government
concentrated its strength on cracking Medelin and Cali drug groups.
</P>
<P>
With the arrest of the Galeano brothers, Colombian police have
seized more than 40 leaders of drug groups and about 9,000 drug
dealers in the country. 
</P>
