<HEADLINE> Marovic Re-elected as Montenegro Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 15 (Xinhua) - Svetozar Marovic, speaker of last
Montenegro parliament, has been re-elected by the first meeting of
the new parliament.
</P>
<P>
Forty parliamentary members of The Coalition for Better Life
led by Montenegro president Milo Djukanovic voted him in, while 26
parliamentarians of the Socialist People's Party, led by Prime
Minister Momir Bulatovic of Yugoslavia voted against him.
</P>
<P>
After being elected, Marovic expressed hope for extensive
co-operation between various political parties in Montenegro and
Yugoslavia. He said there was hope for this if everyone learned
how to understand each other and make compromises.
</P>
<P>
The Coalition for Better Life won the parliamentary election on
May 31, gaining 42 seats of the 78-seat parliament. The Socialist
People's Party, its main rival, won 29 seats.
</P>
<P>
It is widely believed the United States-favored Djukanovic
victory, and the consolidation of his power over the pro-Belgrade
Bulatovic will have a far-reaching influence on the political
situation of both Montenegro and Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
