<HEADLINE> Storms Hit Romania, Killing Some Ten People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Heavy storms that hit Romania
over the past few days have killed about 10 people, local media
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A dozen people were struck by lightning, and two of them were
killed instantly. Others suffered serious burns.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,500 houses and thousands of hectares of farmland were
destroyed. The economic loss was estimated at dozens of billions of
leu (one U.S. dollar equals to 8,500 leu).
</P>
<P>
Eleven counties in eastern and northern Romania suffered most,
where the rainfall reached 115 liter per square meter.
</P>
<P>
In Bacau County alone, more than 1,000 cattle were drowned. The
storms also cut traffic and power supply in many towns and
villages.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Minister of Water, Forests and Environmental
Protection Romica Tomescu has briefed the prime minister about the
disasters and called for emergency measures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
