<HEADLINE> Love Affairs Top Matters of Privacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey shows that the
majority of Chinese women place their highest priority on
"personal love affairs" in terms of privacy, a sharp contrast to
western women who place priority on age.
</P>
<P>
The survey of 750 women between the ages of 18-65 revealed
that 64.3 percent of respondents agreed that "personal love
affairs" ranked first in terms of privacy.
</P>
<P>
Some 6-9 percent of respondents listed "diaries", "income" and
"past experiences" as private matters.
</P>
<P>
The survey also reflected that the fact that Chinese women
between the ages of 21-30, college graduates, high income earners
and professionals accounted for the majority of respondents who
listed "personal love affairs" as the top priority.  
</P>
