<HEADLINE> Border City Exports Vegetables to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Dongning County located on the
border separating China and Russia is serving as a major vegetable
supplier for eight million residents living in the easternmost
regions of Russia.
</P>
<P>
More than 60 trucks carrying fresh vegetables, fruit
and light industrial goods depart the Dongning frontier station
each morning bound for Russian cities.
</P>
<P>
The port opened to the outside world in 1989 and has since
handled over 1.2 million tons of export goods with a total foreign
trade value of one billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The county, which is blessed with a mild climate and fertile
land, grows vegetable on over 4,000 ha and fruits on some 8,000
hectares. Dongning recorded a 1997 business turnover of 150
million yuan on exported of over 68,000 tons of fruits and
vegetables.
</P>
<P>
Dongning has attempted to expand its market share by
constructing a wholesale center and Chinese goods market in
Russia. The facility, which covers 150,000 sq.m. and employs over
10,000 Chinese citizens, has an annual trade value of 1.5 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
