<HEADLINE> Graf Seeded Fourth for Wimbledon Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Former world number one Steffi Graf
of Germany was seeded fourth for Wimbledon Open tennis
Championships on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Graf, back in action at Edgbaston tennis last week after
suffering a hamstring injury in March, has been given a special
rating of number three in the world by the Women's Tennis
Association to protect her seeding in tournaments.
</P>
<P>
Officially now ranked 91st, Graf will be bidding for her eighth
Wimbledon singles title and 22nd Grand Slam victory when the
championships begin next Monday.
</P>
<P>
Graf is seeded behind world number one Martina Hingis of
Switzerland, Lindsay Davenport of the United States and Jana
Novotna of Czech Republic, but ahead of French Open champion
Spaniard Arantxa Sanchez Vicario, seeded five, and her old rival
American Monica Seles, sixth seed.
</P>
<P>
American Pete Sampras, winner of four Wimbledon titles in five
years, heads the men's seedings. Chilean Marcelo Rios is second.
</P>
<P>
French Open champion Carlos Moya of Sapin is fifth while the
resurgent Andre Agassi of the United States has been ranked 13th
seed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
