<HEADLINE> Axworthy Concerned by Statements of Iranian Opposition Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Foreign Minister Lloyd
Axworthy expressed deep concern Monday over the recent statements
by the Iranian opposition Mujahedin Khalq Organization (MKO).
</P>
<P>
The MKO, which espouses violence in pursuit of its cause, said
that it intends to step up its international activities against
the government of Iran.
</P>
<P>
"Canada finds these threats completely unacceptable. We condemn
terrorism, whatever the source," said Axworthy. "We will not
tolerate any actions directed against the legitimate interests of
other countries, or their accredited representatives, on Canadian
soil," he added.
</P>
<P>
The latest threats come in the wake of a recent bombing of a
courthouse in Teheran, which resulted in fatalities and for which
the MKO claimed responsibility.
</P>
<P>
Known members of the MKO are not permitted to enter Canada.
</P>
</TEXT>
