<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Chinese Kidnap Victims Freed by Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Five kidnapped Chinese were freed
Monday morning after a joint operation between London police and
their Chinese counterparts, a Metropolitan police spokesman said
Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
They were released and over 50 suspects were arrested in early
Monday morning raids on seven houses in London, Kent and Essex,
and more than 200 police officers were involved in the operation,
said Jeffrey Rees, detective chief superintendant in the New
Scotland Yard.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese men, aged between 20 to 35, all recently arrived in
Britain illegally from China's southern province Fujian. They were
held up and asked to pay 250,000 Chinese currency yuan by their
family members back in China.
</P>
<P>
Another suspect was arrested in China involved in the kidnap
case, Rees told reporters in his office.
</P>
<P>
All five hostages were beaten and threatened to be killed
during their eight-day ordeal, which began on June 7. Rees said he
believed the kidnapping is the largest in Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980616.0308 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Plunge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 15 (Xinhua) -- The Dow industrials plunged more
than 200 points Monday, hitting a three-month low, as pessimism
grew over the market for a recovery of the Japanese economy.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average sank 207.01 points to
8,627.93. The 2.4 percent loss represents the fifth largest
point-drop ever. This is also its biggest point loss since early
January and the lowest finish since March 13.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators also tumbled as nervous currency
traders sent the Japanese yen down to an eight-year low against
the dollar.
</P>
<P>
Monday's loss cut the Dow's gain for 1998 to 9 percent, down
from a peak of 16.5 percent at the May 13 record close of
9,211.84.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 fell 21.83 to 1,077.01, and the
technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 29.31 to 1,715.75.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by a more than a 3-to-1 margin
on the New York Stock Exchange, where NYSE volume totaled 582.90
million shares, down from 631.64 Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 11.78 to 554.89, and the American
Stock Exchange composite index fell 13.52 to 683.88.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 7.73 to 433.86.
</P>
<P>
The dollar's rise and the flight from stocks pushed the bond
market higher, where long-term interest rates sank to another
all-time low. 
</P>
</TEXT>
