<HEADLINE> Germany Beat United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, June 15 (Xinhua) -- Jurgen Klinsmann scored a superb goal
at the 64th minute to wrap up the match 2-0 for Germany in a Group F
match here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The German team played quite relaxed in the first half and took
an early lead at the 8th minute when Andy Moller got a pass from
Klinsmann and headed it home.
</P>
<P>
Being one goal behind, the American team geared up and played
more aggressively in a bid to get an equaliser. The German team
took the chance to launch some quick counter-attacks but most of
their shots were blocked by the American defence line.
</P>
<P>
The second half was more balance than the first one as the
American team controlled the midfield and outshot their German
counterparts. But their poor finishing let down all their efforts.
</P>
<P>
The German team, once being forced to defence, had a
counter-attack at the 64th minute. Oliver Bierhoff sent a long
over-head pass to Klinsmann while the latter chested down the ball
and beat the American goalie with a volley.
</P>
<P>
Bierhoff, who help the German team win the European Championship
in 1996, put up a disappointing performance. He squandered several
chances and seemed have difficulty with the American tight defence.
</P>
</TEXT>
